'''Jalandhara Bandha''' ([[International Phonetic Alphabet|IPA]]:/ɟɐːl̺n̺d̺ʱɐrɐ bɐndʱɐ/; {{lang-sa | जालन्धर बंध}},<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.spokensanskrit.de/index.php?id=601369 | title = SpokenSanskrit.de Entry: जालन्धर बंध | accessdate= 2012-03-24}}</ref> [[IAST]]: Jālandhara bandha{{sfn|White|2011|p=261}}{{sfn | Monier-Williams | 1964 | p=[http://www.sanskrit-lexicon.uni-koeln.de/cgi-bin/monier/serveimg.pl?file=/scans/MWScan/MWScanjpg/mw0720-baddhR.jpg 720]}}) is the chin [[Bandha (Yoga)|Bandha]] described and employed in [[Hatha Yoga]].
==Etymology== Jālandhara bandha comes from [[Sanskrit]]. Jāla {{lang-sa|जाल}} means web<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.spokensanskrit.de/index.php?script=DI&beginning=0+&tinput=jAla&trans=Translate&direction=AU | title=SpokenSanskrit.de Entry: जाल | accessdate=2012-03-24}}</ref> or "net"{{sfn|Macdonell|2005|p=99}} and dhara ({{lang-sa|धर}}) means "holding".<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.spokensanskrit.de/index.php?script=DI&beginning=0+&tinput=dhara+&trans=Translate&direction=AU | title=SpokenSanskrit.de Entry: धर | accessdate=2012-03-24}}</ref> Bandha ({{lang-sa|बंध}}) means "bond; contracting".{{sfn | Monier-Williams | 1964 | p=[http://www.sanskrit-lexicon.uni-koeln.de/cgi-bin/monier/serveimg.pl?file=/scans/MWScan/MWScanjpg/mw0720-baddhR.jpg 720]}}
==Description== It is performed by extending the neck and elevating the [[sternum]] (breastbone) before dropping the head so that the chin may rest on the chest. Meanwhile the tongue pushes up against the palate in the mouth. {{sfn|Ramaswami|2005|p = 4}}
